        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is browning, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine 2/3<strong> </strong>of your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> in a small bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[110ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml] </span><strong>cold<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>water</strong> – this is your<strong> Filipino-style tocino sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
